alt: Photo by Steph on June 15, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'Don't stress about sizes'
caption:
Styling for your size!! - 
For my first post during this series I wanted to take a look at sizing and discuss the issues surrounding it. I’ve had countless experiences in changing rooms while trying on clothes where I have been dishearten by not fitting into my usual size (12). However after years of  shopping from different brands and looking at different styles - especially jeans, I’ve come to understand I will never be classed as a size 12 alone, but a multitude of sizes based upon the clothing itself. 
I’ve included photos of me wearing different jeans and included there sizes which range from a 12-16 as well as styles that are mom jeans, skinny jeans, cargo pants and shorts. 
My main takeaway from discovering the difference in sizing is not to get hung up on the label inside, if the jeans you have on are a 16 but you normally fit into a 12 who cares? If they look good and feel good that is all that matters ! 💞 •
•
